Description
	Magnesium is the ninth most abundant element in the universe
 and eight most abundant element in the Earth's crust. It is ashiny 
gray solid which bears a close physical resemblance to the other five
elements in the second column of the periodic table. Magnesium is
highly flammable, especially when powdered or shaved into thin strips,
though  it is difficult to ignite in mass or bulk. 	           